JOHANNESBURG &#8211; South Africa&#8217;s National Union of Mineworkers (NUM) has signed a three-year wage agreement with petrochemical firm Sasol&#8217;s mining unit, the labour union said on Thursday.The lowest-paid employees will receive a 7% wage increase from December 1, the NUM said in a statement. Sasol&#8217;s share price was up 1.52% at R377.19 at the close.